# Create Brownian Motion
import numpy as np
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import seaborn as sns

sns.set(color_codes=True)
# settings for seaborn plot sizes
sns.set(rc={'figure.figsize':(20,5)})

# Model parameters
t_start = 0
t_end = 200
length = 5000
sigma = 1
r = -3

# Define time axis
t = np.linspace(t_start, t_end, length)
dt = np.mean(np.diff(t))

# Initial conditions
x = np.zeros(length)
x[0] = np.random.normal(loc=0.0, scale=1.0)

# Define terms in pitchfork bifurcation
alpha1 = lambda x,t: r*x
alpha2 = lambda x,t: np.power(x,3)
diffusion = lambda x,t: sigma
noise = np.random.normal(loc=0.0,scale=1.0,size=length)*np.sqrt(dt)

# Solve the SDE
for i in range(1,length):
    x[i] = x[i-1] + alpha1(x[i-1], i*dt)*dt - alpha2(x[i-1], i*dt)*dt + diffusion(x[i-1],i*dt)*noise[i]


plt.figure()
ax1 = plt.plot(t,x)
ax2.set(xlabel='days', ylabel='X')

plt.figure()
ax2 = sns.distplot(x,
                  bins=100,
                  kde=True,
                  color='skyblue',
                  hist_kws={"linewidth": 15,'alpha':0.1})

ax2.set(xlabel='X', ylabel='Frequency')

import numpy as np
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import matplotlib.animation as animation
from matplotlib import animation, rc
from IPython.display import HTML

N=len(x)
y = x[0:N]
t2 = t[0:N]

fig, ax = plt.subplots()
line, = ax.plot(t2, y, color='k')

def init():
    line.set_data([], [])
    return (line,)

def animate(t,y,i):
    line.set_data(t2, y)
    return (line,)

def update(num, t2, y, line):
    line.set_data(t2[:num], x[:num])
    line.axes.axis([t_start, t_end, np.min(y), np.max(y)])
    return line,

# anim = animation.FuncAnimation(fig, animate, init_func=init,
#                                frames=100, interval=20, blit=True)

ani = animation.FuncAnimation(fig, update, len(y), fargs=[t2, y, line],
                              interval=25, blit=True)

HTML(ani.to_html5_video())

def find_nearest(array, value):
    array = np.asarray(array)
    idx = (np.abs(array - value)).argmin()
    return idx

counts, bins, bars = plt.hist(x,bins=Nbins)

counts2 = []
for i in range(len(x)):
    n = find_nearest(bins,x[i])
    if n>len(counts)-1:
        n = len(counts)-1
    counts2.append(counts[n])

fig, ax = plt.subplots()
N0 = np.max(counts2)/np.max(data[100]._y) * 1.15
line2, = plt.plot(data[100]._x,data[100]._y*N0, linewidth=10, color='r')
line, = ax.plot(x, counts2, marker='o', markersize=30)

data=ax2.get_children()

    
def init():
    line.set_data([], [])
    return (line,)

def animate(x,counts,i):
    line.set_data(x, counts)
    return (line,)

def update(num, x, counts, line):
    line2.set_data(data[100]._x,data[100]._y*N0)
    line.set_data(x[num], counts2[num])
    line2.axes.axis([np.min(x)*1.1, np.max(x)*1.1, 0, np.max(counts2)*1.25])
    line.axes.axis([np.min(x)*1.1, np.max(x)*1.1, 0, np.max(counts2)*1.25])
    return line,


plt.figure()

plt.plot(x[0],counts[find_nearest(bins,x[0])],marker='o',markersize=30)
plt.xlim([np.min(x)*1.1,np.max(x)*1.1])

ani = animation.FuncAnimation(fig, update, len(x), fargs=[x, counts2, line],
                              interval=25, blit=True)

HTML(ani.to_html5_video())
